## Building a Multi-step Form (Wizard) in Vue 3

**Mental model:** A wizard is one shared reactive form object plus a current step index. Each step reads/writes the same object; Next/Back move the index with bounds; a `computed` gates advancing per step. Submit only on the last step.

### Step 1 — Shared data + step index
```vue
<script setup>
import { reactive, ref, computed } from 'vue';
const step = ref(0);
const data = reactive({ name: '', email: '', plan: 'free' });
</script>
```

### Step 2 — Per-step validation as computed
```js
const valid = computed(() => {
  if (step.value === 0) return data.name.trim().length > 0;
  if (step.value === 1) return /.+@.+\..+/.test(data.email);
  return true;
});
```

### Step 3 — Navigation with bounds
```js
const next = () => { if (valid.value) step.value = Math.min(step.value + 1, steps.length - 1); };
const back = () => { step.value = Math.max(step.value - 1, 0); };
```

### Step 4 — Stepper + conditional submit
```vue
<button v-if="step === steps.length - 1" @click="submit">Submit</button>
<button v-else :disabled="!valid" @click="next">Next</button>
```

**Edge cases**

| Case | Handling |
| :-- | :-- |
| Next spam | `valid` gate + `Math.min` clamp. |
| Back keeps data | Shared `reactive` object persists. |
| Review | Bind directly to the same `data`. |

**Interview tip:** Use a single `reactive` data object plus `v-model` per field — it keeps every step in sync without prop-drilling and makes the final review a direct read of `data`.

