## Building a Multi-step Form (Wizard) in Angular

**Mental model:** A wizard is one shared data object plus a current step index on the component. Each step reads/writes the same object; Next/Back move the index with bounds; a getter gates advancing per step. Submit only on the last step. Classic `NgModule` setup, no `?.`/`??` (the build rejects them), no `FormsModule` — bind with `[value]`/`(input)`.

### Step 1 — Shared data + index
```typescript
step = 0;
data = { name: '', email: '', plan: 'free' };
steps = ['Account', 'Contact', 'Review'];
```

### Step 2 — Validation getter
```typescript
get valid(): boolean {
  if (this.step === 0) { return this.data.name.trim().length > 0; }
  if (this.step === 1) { return /.+@.+\..+/.test(this.data.email); }
  return true;
}
```

### Step 3 — Navigation with bounds
```typescript
next(): void { if (this.valid) { this.step = Math.min(this.step + 1, this.steps.length - 1); } }
back(): void { this.step = Math.max(this.step - 1, 0); }
```

### Step 4 — Stepper + conditional submit
```html
<button *ngIf="step === steps.length - 1; else nextBtn" (click)="submit()">Submit</button>
<ng-template #nextBtn><button [disabled]="!valid" (click)="next()">Next</button></ng-template>
```

**Edge cases**

| Case | Handling |
| :-- | :-- |
| Next spam | `valid` gate + `Math.min` clamp. |
| Back keeps data | One shared `data` object. |
| Review | Read the same object in the last step. |

**Interview tip:** A single `data` object updated via `(input)` (no `FormsModule`) keeps the wizard dependency-free, and the validation getter recomputed per change detection cleanly gates the Next button.

